 Cookhouse - A 32-year-old woman and a 43-year-old man are due to appear in Somerset-East Magistrate's Court on Friday for alleged drug dealing. "On Wednesday, at about 20:00, an off-duty police official stationed at Cookhouse Operational Command Centre received information from a source about mandrax tablets being sold at premises in the Bongweni locality of Cookhouse," said police spokesperson, Captain Lariane Jonker. "After mobilizing all off-duty Operational Command Centre members as well as the on-duty Visible Policing members, a search warrant was executed at the identified homestead. "During the operation, a total of 591 mandrax tablets were confiscated with an estimated street value of R36 000." The 32-year-old female and the 43-year-old male will appear on charges relating to Dealing in Mandrax at the Somerset-East Magistrate’s Court on Friday. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 